  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3392",
  "title": "Eventhandler when finished/rendered",
  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe 🙏**\r\n\r\nThere is no \"finished/rendered\" event to do something after the hits are loaded/refreshed. The only available event is the `on.render` or `searchFunction`, but this is too early if you want to do something with the new DOM hits/filters or show something after everything is loaded\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like 🤔**\r\n\r\nA new event to be called after the search/hits are done and build. Simple `on.finished/rendered` function.\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered ✨**\r\n\r\nWith the current `on.render` or `searchFunction` this can't be achieved\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\n\r\nhttps://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/instantsearch/js/?language=js#events",
